<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by Azumi on 06-11-2002 11:21 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I play alot of MMORPGs so maybe a few of these suggestions only apply to them, but ill try anyway.
1. Shortkeys for your magic and health potions , ctrl + 1 or something like that , so you dont get distracted whilst in combat. 
2. (already suggested ) a stand ground key , ie when this key is held down , no matter where you left click it will stay on the spot.
3. Re-spawns , i just dont like going back to the menu to load a saved game.Maybe the guy you first meet's house is the respawn point. If no respawn then maybe autosaves and when you die you instantly go back to the last save.  
4. There should be more of a perminant weapons and armor shop ( maybe there is ) because i dont know if that guy you trade with for weapons is supposed to lock his door but he did with me and now i cant find anywhere to buy weapons. 
5. Monster and Your health should be above your head so that you can watch it more carefully.
6. Get rid of the silly words when you pull a lever ... i mean i walked around pulling levers and they ALL open doors, so after the first time i would say its fairly obvious what it has done and he should no longer ask what.  
7. Restrict certain areas to certain lvls , a lvl requirement probably would have stopped me finishing the demo at lvl 1. 
8. NPC's should NOT attack you for a simple mistake.  I picked up a carrot in the weapons trader place and he asked if i was interested in it , i said no and he killed me. ... Instead of doing that why dont you remove the item from inventory when i say no.  

These suggestions are probably to my personal liking.  I understand many people have many personal preferences that others may or may not like. 
lemme know what you think 
-azumi  </TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
